We are building a high-performance team that is excited by complex engineering challenges and is passionate about making transportation safer, more affordable and accessible for all.

Building a self-driving vehicle requires gathering a huge amount of data. At Argo AI we have a fleet of cars driving on city streets and recording everything the car does into vehicle logs. The Data Core team owns the first two stages of processing these logs; ingesting the logs from the cars to the cloud, and processing the logs in the cloud. The infrastructure built by this team processes terabytes of data using the latest technologies.

What you'll do:

Build Argo's scalable on premise as well as cloud based vehicle logs ingest and processing systems
Independently design and deliver end to end solutions
Develop and operate Argo's production ingest system across multiple regions
Establish engineering best practices, and participate in code/architecture reviews
Work closely with vehicle operations, autonomy integration, and development teams to identify key features to improve overall delivery of critical features to the AV

What we're looking for:

Degree in Computer Engineering, Computer Science, Electrical Engineering, Robotics or a related field
Experience with scaling cloud and on premise systems
Experience building highly available systems
Experience with back-end services and big data technologies
Broad software development and architectural skills
Strong knowledge of cloud technologies including AWS, GCP, Kubernetes, and similar products
Excellent communication skills are required given our distributed and diverse team

