Sensor calibration and integrity is a core technical problem for L4 self driving vehicles and a critical component for making autonomous vehicles safe. Calibration and Sensor Integrity team is responsible for the software and algorithms for calibrating Argo's fleet at scale and for online monitoring and reporting the integrity of perception sensors. The team works on offboard software for high quality calibration of lidars, cameras, IMUs and radars in production within a limited space and time budget. The team is also responsible for problems unique to building L4 self driving including onboard calibration validation and detection of reduced sensor performance such as sensor degradation, obstructions like dirt and water and estimation of external conditions such as fog. As a member of the team you will have the opportunity to work on different sensor modalities and apply computer vision and machine learning tools. Your work will have significant cross-functional impact across Perception, Hardware and Operations teams.

